members.name: getExitLocation
members.comment: Gets the location that entities are teleported to when entering the gateway portal. If this block state is not placed the location's world will be null.

members.name: setExitLocation
members.comment: Sets the exit location that entities are teleported to when they enter the gateway portal. If this block state is not placed the location's world has to be null.

throws: IllegalArgumentException - for differing worlds

members.name: isExactTeleport
members.comment: Gets whether this gateway will teleport entities directly to the exit location instead of finding a nearby location.

return: true if the gateway is teleporting to the exact location

members.name: setExactTeleport
members.comment: Sets whether this gateway will teleport entities directly to the exit location instead of finding a nearby location.

param: exact - whether to teleport to the exact location

members.name: getAge
members.comment: Gets the age in ticks of the gateway. If the age is less than 200 ticks a magenta beam will be emitted, whilst if it is a multiple of 2400 ticks a purple beam will be emitted.

members.name: setAge
members.comment: Sets the age in ticks of the gateway. If the age is less than 200 ticks a magenta beam will be emitted, whilst if it is a multiple of 2400 ticks a purple beam will be emitted.

name: org.bukkit.block.EndGateway
comment: Represents a captured state of an end gateway.
